DysruptionHub reports: Jacksonville, Texas, took some city systems offline after detecting suspicious network activity Friday, leaving some online services unavailable Monday as officials investigated a cybersecurity incident. The city said it detected the activity July 3 and later determined it was related to a cybersecurity incident. Officials took affected systems offline, disabled some systems as...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F07%2F07%2Fjacksonville-texas-keeps-some-city-systems-offline-after-cyber-incident%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Djacksonville-texas-keeps-some-city-systems-offline-after-cyber-incident&amp;action_name=Jacksonville%2C%20Texas%2C%20keeps%20some%20city%20systems%20offline%20after%20cyber%20incident&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
